<FIRST>r i PM-Bush-FenderBender     02-25 0151</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Bush-Fender Bender,0152</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bush's Motorcade Involved In Fender Bender</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Bush Rdp, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two U.S. diplomatic cars had a minor collision today
as President Bush's motorcade arrived on the rain-swept tarmac at
Haneda Airport for his departure to China.
   Reporters heard the loud crunch of a collision and saw that one
car toward the back of the line had stopped suddenly and the driver
behind had been unable to stop in time. There appeared to be no
injuries and no damage beyond bumper dents.
   Bush's limousine was toward the front of the motorcade and was
not affected by the accident. His plane took off a few minutes later
for Beijing, where he is to continue his Asian swing before
returning home to Washington next week.
   At least 60 people and two dogs with handlers were posted on
security duty around Bush's Air Force plane on the tarmac.
</TEXT>
