<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--BuddhaArrests     02-25 0145</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Buddha Arrests,0149</SECOND>
<HEAD>Court Fines Two Americans For Desecrating Buddha</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Thai court fined two Americans for
desecrating a Buddha after a photography session in which the model
posed in her underwear beside the statue, police said today.
   The court in the southern island resort of Phuket sentenced
photographer Sante Maria D'Razzio, 33, of New Jersey, and Kara Ruth
Young, a 23-year-old model from California, to pay $118 each in
fines, said police Sub. Lt. Amnuey Kraiwuttianant. It also gave each
18-month suspended jail terms.
   Hometowns of the pair were not released.
   Authorities said they faced up to seven years in prison.
   The pair were arrested Sunday after a picture-taking session for
the French magazine Vogue inside Chung Len Buddhist temple. Police
said Ms. Young had been posing by a Buddha in her underwear.
   Thailand is a predominately Buddhist country.
</TEXT>
