<TEXT>
   Zambia's largest shoe factory was shut down
Saturday, and executives cited a shortage of imported raw materials
as the reason.
   The Bata Shoe Company, which supplies four-fifths of this
nation's shoes, said half its 30 shoe shops were also closed. The
move affected up to 1,000 workers.
