<HEAD>Missing Passengers Were On Vacations, Business Trips</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Plane Emergency, Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto LA2</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are brief sketches of the six Americans who were among the
nine passengers blown out of a United Airlines jumbo jet shortly
after it left Honolulu.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Susan and Harry Craig of Morristown, N.J., were on their way to
New Zealand for a vacation, said their daughter Carolyn Craig.
   ``It was like a second honeymoon for them,'' she said. The couple
had been married 23 years.
   Craig, 42, and his wife, 41, were managers for AT&amp;T
</TEXT>
