<HEAD>12-Year-Old Charged With Killing Mother, Wounding Father</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ASPEN HILL, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 12-year-old boy has been charged as a
juvenile with murder and attempted murder in connection with the
fatal shooting of his mother and the wounding of his father, police
said Saturday.
   Matthew Nupp was being held at the Alfred Knolls Juvenile
Detention Center in Rockville after he allegedly shot his mother
three times with a .22 caliber hunting rifle Friday.
   Police said Nupp, a student at Parkland Junior High School in
