father, who managed to telephone police.
   James Nupp was taken to an area hospital where he suffered one
gunshot wound to the neck, another to the chest and was grazed by a
third bullet. He remained in fair condition Saturday.
   Matthew later surrendered to police who surrounded the home. The
boy's 7-year-old brother fled the house unharmed, and an
unidentified 3-year-old also was not harmed.
