<HEAD>Karpov and Ivanchuk Share Top Place After Six Rounds</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LINARES, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former world champion Anatoli Karpov and
fellow Soviet Vasili Ivanchuk shared first place Saturday in the
Seventh City of Linares chess tournament.
   Karpov defeated Ljubomir Ljubojevic of Yugoslavia and Ivanchuk
drew with his countryman Alexander Yusupov during the sixth round of
play.
   There were two other draws Saturday: Lakos Portisch of Hungary
against Soviet Andrei Sokolov, and Jan Timman of the Netherlands
against Alexander Beliavsky of the Soviet Union.
   The match between Nigel Short of Britain and Boris Gulko of the
United States was adjourned. Johan Hjartarson, Iceland, did not play
Saturday.
   Karpov and Ivanchuk shared top place of the standings with four
points each; Ljubojevic and Yusupov were second with three each;
Hjartarson, Gulko and Portisch, two each; and Short, Timman, Sokolov
and Beliavsky, each with 1.5 points.
