<FIRST>r a AM-TwiceLucky     02-25 0181</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Twice Lucky,0184</SECOND>
<HEAD>Trucker Hits Lottery Again _ This Time For $7 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALLENTOWN, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Edward Stephen Pohl said he doesn't believe
he has extrasensory perception _ even if his initials are ESP _ but
he had enough foresight to play the lottery and won $7 million, his
second big lottery haul.
   Several years ago, the truck driver plunked down $5 on 3227 in a
Pennsylvania Lottery game, and he walked away with $25,000.
   Then, on Jan. 13, his 61st birthday and a Friday, Pohl had a
lucky hunch.
   ``I had this feeling I was going to hit the lottery,'' Pohl
recalled last week. ``I told my wife we were going to hit this week.
So I bought $30 worth of tickets'' for the Super Seven drawing of
Jan. 18.
   The Pohl magic had come through again. This time it was worth
$7.158 million.
   ``It's nice for me because I'm going to retire and it will be
good for my kids,'' he said. ``This just goes to show you that
Friday the 13th isn't so unlucky after all.''
